The paper deals with property testing of Boolean functions, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of adaptive and non-adaptive testers suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The focus on hypercubes and ordered ranges suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of query complexity and testing for unateness suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
